						               													<description>It&amp;rsquo;s October 1931 in Seattle Washington, and you&amp;rsquo;ve had a tough couple of years. The Stock Market crash of &amp;rsquo;29 brought on hard times. You lost your job last year when the lumber mill shut down. Nobody&amp;rsquo;s hiring. The local bank where you kept your money saved made loans to those businesses that were shutting down. Depositors panicked and there was a run. The bank went into receivership, and your savings were wiped out. With no job and no savings you couldn&amp;rsquo;t make your house payment, and your mortgage was foreclosed on. Like millions of Americans you find yourself jobless, penniless, homeless.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Down by the Port, on the site of the old shipyard, some men are gathering supplies for winter: cardboard boxes, tar paper, firewood. You have decided to join their shantytown and to try to start again.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Who will eat the most food? Who will wear the least tattered clothes? Who will live in the finest hovel? Who will become The Mayor of Hooverville?&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
